HEADWORD: Albata
<hw>Al*ba"ta</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>albatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>albare</ets> to make white, fr.
<ets>albus</ets> white.]</ety> <def>A white metallic alloy; which is
made into spoons, forks, teapots, etc. British plate or German silver.
See <cref>German silver</cref>, under <er>German</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

